  "texts": [
    "Makhortykh 2023a; Simon and Zucker 2020) is an important task.",
    "Its importance is particularly pronounced when considering the impact of robotic agents on communicating memories about particularly sensitive and traumatic episodes of the past such as genocides.",
    "Another related matter concerns the question of the regulation of human-to-robot and robot-to-robot memory communication.",
    "While the discussion of memory-related regulatory mechanisms has intensified in the last decade, it has primarily been focused on the protection of individual privacy in the context of human interactions with AI-driven information retrieval systems (i.e.",
    "the right to be forgotten/the right for erasure in relation to search engines; Ausloos 2012; Esposito 2017)."
